text: Filip Forejtek (born 3 November 1997 in Plzeň) is a Czech alpine skier. He competed in the 2018 Winter Olympics. His brother Jonáš is a professional tennis player, his mother’s father Pavel Macenauer represented Czechoslovakia in tennis singles at the 1924 Olympic Games. ==References== Category:1997 births Category:Living people Category:Alpine skiers at the 2018 Winter Olympics Category:Czech male alpine skiers Category:Olympic alpine skiers of the Czech Republic
